1331c9176233b177,48996,"According to so-called ‘special’ parental liability, parents are liable for damage inflicted on another by their chile if the supervision is not the responsibility of the parents but another person and the damage occurred due to the poor upbringing of the minor or the poor example or bad habits set by the parents, or if the damage can otherwise be attributed to their culpability (Article 145(1) OZ).",the damage,explicit,can,permission,attributed|occurred,"if the supervision is not the responsibility of the parents but another person and the damage occurred due to the poor upbringing of the minor or the poor example or bad habits set by the parents , or if the damage can otherwise be attributed to their culpability ( Article 145(1 ) OZ )",,True,"According to so-called ‘special’ parental liability, parents are liable for damage inflicted on another by their chile if the supervision is not the responsibility of the parents but another person and the damage occurred due to the poor upbringing of the minor or the poor example or bad habits set by the parents, or if the damage can otherwise be attributed to their culpability (Article 145(1) OZ).",rule_candidate,payoff,choice|payoff,2,0,0,1,0,0,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
1331c9176233b177,48999,"Just liability: (1) If the damage was inflicted by a person who is not liable and compensation cannot be obtained from the liable superviso r, the court may order the perpetrator to compens ate all or part of the damage if justice demands, particularly in light of the financial situations of the perpetrator and the victim (Article 146(1) OZ).",Just liability : ( 1 ),explicit,can,prohibition,obtained,"If the damage was inflicted by a person who is not liable and compensation|if justice demands , particularly in light of the financial situations of the perpetrator and the victim ( Article 146(1 ) OZ",,True,"Just liability: (1) If the damage was inflicted by a person who is not liable and compensation cannot be obtained from the liable superviso r, the court may order the perpetrator to compens ate all or part of the damage if justice demands, particularly in light of the financial situations of the perpetrator and the victim (Article 146(1) OZ).",rule_candidate,payoff,choice|payoff,2,0,0,1,0,0,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
