1331c9176233b177,49449,"In trademark law, the Court of Cassation has held ""that the mere infringement of the pri vate right of ownership of a trademark justifies the award of damages"" (Cass., com., 8 March 2005, No 02-20.675, cited by L. Gratton, Le dommage déduit de la faute, RTD civ., 2013, p. 275), pointing out, once again, that the damage suffered by the trademark owner cannot be left without compensation, while specifying the form that the compensation must take.",the damage suffered by the trademark owner,explicit,can,prohibition,left,while specifying the form that the compensation must take|without compensation,,True,"It thus appears that certain faults necessarily result in damage, which itself entails, at the very least, non-material damage which the court cannot leave without compensation.",rule_candidate,payoff,choice|payoff,2,0,0,1,0,0,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
