1331c9176233b177,49674,"If a natural person is injured or his or her health is otherwise damaged, the person liable for the damage shall be obliged to compensate the victim for any loss or non-material damage suffered by him or her.",,implicit,shall,obligation,obliged,If a natural person is injured or his or her health is otherwise damaged,,True,"If a natural person is injured or his or her health is otherwise damaged, the person liable for the damage shall be obliged to compensate the victim for any loss or non-material damage suffered by him or her.",rule_candidate,payoff,choice|payoff,2,0,0,1,0,0,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
1331c9176233b177,49690,"The Supreme Court has clarified that, in order to determine the extent of the non-pecu niary damage to be compensated in a particular case, the court must apply the criteria for assessing the amount of that damage in monetary terms to the extent possibl e. Furthermore, in order to determine the extent of non -material damage, it is necessary to assess, on a case -by-case basis, the whole set of criteria, that is to say, both the circumstances which may lead to a higher amount of non- material damage and the circumstances which may lead to a lower amount of compensation (see, for example, the ruling of the Chamber of Judges of the Civil Cases Division of the Supreme Court in civil proceedings, P.D.v.",the court,explicit,must,obligation,apply the criteria,in order to determine the extent of the non - pecu niary damage to be compensated in a particular case|for assessing the amount of that damage in monetary terms to the extent possibl e. Furthermore,,True,"The Supreme Court has clarified that, in order to determine the extent of the non-pecu niary damage to be compensated in a particular case, the court must apply the criteria for assessing the amount of that damage in monetary terms to the extent possibl e. Furthermore, in order to determine the extent of non -material damage, it is necessary to assess, on a case -by-case basis, the whole set of criteria, that is to say, both the circumstances which may lead to a higher amount of non- material damage and the circumstances which may lead to a lower amount of compensation (see, for example, the ruling of the Chamber of Judges of the Civil Cases Division of the Supreme Court in civil proceedings, P.D.v.",rule_candidate,boundary,boundary|choice|information|payoff,4,1,0,1,1,0,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
