14ad78141c72ae5d,61040,"(e) T ERMINATION.—On and after the date that is one year after the date on which the President imposes sanctions under subsection (c) with respect to a person, the President may terminate the application of such sanctions with respect to that person if the President submits to the appropriate congressional committees a certification that— (1) the Government of Turkey and any person acting on its behalf no longer possesses the S–400 air defense system or a successor system; (2) no S-400 air defense system or successor system is operated or maintained inside Turkey by nationals of the Rus- sian Federation or persons acting on behalf of the Government of the Russian Federation or the defense sector of the Russian Federation; and (3) the President has received reliable assurances from the Government of Turkey that the Government of Turkey will not knowingly engage, or allow any foreign person to engage on its behalf, in pursuing any activity subject to sanc- tions under section 231 of the Countering America’s Adversaries Through Sanctions Act (22 U.S.C. 9525) to reacquire the S- 400 air defense system or a successor system.",the President,explicit,may,permission,terminate the application of such sanctions with respect to that person|operated|maintained|received reliable assurances from the Government of Turkey that the Government of Turkey will not knowingly engage|allow,if the President submits to the appropriate congressional committees a certification that — ( 1 ) the Government of Turkey and any person acting on its behalf no longer possesses the S–400 air defense system or a successor system|subject to sanc- tions under section 231 of the Countering America’s Adversaries Through Sanctions Act (22 U.S.C. 9525) to reacquire the S- 400 air defense system or a successor system.,system,True,"(e) T ERMINATION.—On and after the date that is one year after the date on which the President imposes sanctions under subsection (c) with respect to a person, the President may terminate the application of such sanctions with respect to that person if the President submits to the appropriate congressional committees a certification that— (1) the Government of Turkey and any person acting on its behalf no longer possesses the S–400 air defense system or a successor system; (2) no S-400 air defense system or successor system is operated or maintained inside Turkey by nationals of the Rus- sian Federation or persons acting on behalf of the Government of the Russian Federation or the defense sector of the Russian Federation; and (3) the President has received reliable assurances from the Government of Turkey that the Government of Turkey will not knowingly engage, or allow any foreign person to engage on its behalf, in pursuing any activity subject to sanc- tions under section 231 of the Countering America’s Adversaries Through Sanctions Act (22 U.S.C. 9525) to reacquire the S- 400 air defense system or a successor system.",rule_candidate,boundary,boundary|choice|payoff,3,1,0,1,0,0,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
