14ad78141c72ae5d,71801,"‘‘(b) A WARDS.— ‘‘(1) IN GENERAL.—In any covered judicial or administrative action, or related action, the Secretary, under regulations pre- scribed by the Secretary, in consultation with the Attorney General and subject to subsection (c) and to amounts made available in advance by appropriation Acts, shall pay an award or awards to 1 or more whistleblowers who voluntarily provided H. R. 6395—1212 original information to the employer of the individual, the Secretary, or the Attorney General, as applicable, that led to the successful enforcement of the covered judicial or adminis- trative action, or related action, in an aggregate amount equal to not more than 30 percent, in total, of what has been collected of the monetary sanctions imposed in the action or related actions.","‘ ‘ ( b ) A WARDS . — ‘ ‘ ( 1 ) IN GENERAL.—In any covered judicial or administrative action , or related action , the Secretary ,",explicit,shall,obligation,pay an award or awards,"subject to subsection (c) and to amounts made available in advance by appropriation Acts, shall pay an award or awards to 1 or more whistleblowers who voluntarily provided H. R. 6395—1212 original information to the employer of the individual, the Secretary, or the Attorney General, as applicable, that led to the successful enforcement of the covered judicial or adminis- trative action, or related action, in an aggregate amount equal to not more than 30 percent, in total, of what has been collected of the monetary sanctions imposed in the action or related actions.|under regulations pre- scribed by the Secretary , in consultation with the Attorney General and subject to subsection ( c ) and",,True,"‘‘(b) A WARDS.— ‘‘(1) IN GENERAL.—In any covered judicial or administrative action, or related action, the Secretary, under regulations pre- scribed by the Secretary, in consultation with the Attorney General and subject to subsection (c) and to amounts made available in advance by appropriation Ac