24e98e84927e2589,110300,"Large discrepancies are often seen when machines make mistakes that a human would not make.27 Figure 3 shows that if we add a small perturbation (noise) to an image of a panda—specifically designed to mislead the image classification model—the algorithm recognizes a gibbon with almost 100% certainty, whereas a human would clearly distinguish between the two images (adversarial machine learning techniques) .28 Measuring AI against human intelligence is problematic, as it can lead to a misleading assessment of the technology.",it,explicit,can,permission,lead,,model,True,"Large discrepancies are often seen when machines make mistakes that a human would not make.27 Figure 3 shows that if we add a small perturbation (noise) to an image of a panda—specifically designed to mislead the image classification model—the algorithm recognizes a gibbon with almost 100% certainty, whereas a human would clearly distinguish between the two images (adversarial machine learning techniques) .28 Measuring AI against human intelligence is problematic, as it can lead to a misleading assessment of the technology.",rule_candidate,information,choice|information,2,0,0,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,,,,,,
