6e50bb42a7856f81,203332,"3. Article 38 of Law 7593 establishes that, if the commission of the violation is proven, those investigated are exposed to the imposition of a fine of 5 to 10 times the value of the damage caused or the equivalent of 5 to 20 minimum wages established in Law 7337 of May 5, 1993, in the event that the damage cannot be proven.",the damage,explicit,can,prohibition,proven,if the commission of the violation is proven,,True,"3. Article 38 of Law 7593 establishes that, if the commission of the violation is proven, those investigated are exposed to the imposition of a fine of 5 to 10 times the value of the damage caused or the equivalent of 5 to 20 minimum wages established in Law 7337 of May 5, 1993, in the event that the damage cannot be proven.",rule_candidate,payoff,choice|payoff|position,3,0,1,1,0,0,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
6e50bb42a7856f81,203353,"of article 9, paragraph 17) of the Regulations of Organization and Functions of the Regulatory Authority (RIOF), it is the responsibility of the General Regulator to order the opening of administrative procedures in which a fine is applied as a sanction, as well as to issue preparatory acts, precautionary measures and the final resolution, in addition to hearing any challenges that may be presented.",that,explicit,may,permission,presented,,,True,"of article 9, paragraph 17) of the Regulations of Organization and Functions of the Regulatory Authority (RIOF), it is the responsibility of the General Regulator to order the opening of administrative procedures in which a fine is applied as a sanction, as well as to issue preparatory acts, precautionary measures and the final resolution, in addition to hearing any challenges that may be presented.",rule_candidate,payoff,choice|payoff|position,3,0,1,1,0,0,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
