6e50bb42a7856f81,203364,"Furthermore, this article defines the concession as the “right that the State grants, after a public bidding process, to commercially exploit a line by means of one or more collective vehicles, such as buses, minibuses, minibuses or similar.” 29732-MP which is the Regulation to Law 7593, in the Regulation Based on the powers granted in Law 7593, in the General Law of Public Administration, in Decree III.—That Article 38, paragraph d) of Law 7593 empowers the Regulatory Authority to process administrative sanctioning procedures against public service providers who engage in “Unauthorized provision of public service (...)” by applying for this purpose the ordinary procedure established in the General Law of Public Administration and indicating that if the violation is proven, it may apply a fine of five to ten times the value of the damage caused that it determines, or, a fine equivalent to 5 to 20 minimum base salaries, established in Law 7337 of May 5, 1993, when it is unable to determine the damage.",it,explicit,may,permission,apply a fine of five,if the violation is proven,service,True,"Furthermore, this article defines the concession as the “right that the State grants, after a public bidding process, to commercially exploit a line by means of one or more collective vehicles, such as buses, minibuses, minibuses or similar.” 29732-MP which is the Regulation to Law 7593, in the Regulation Based on the powers granted in Law 7593, in the General Law of Public Administration, in Decree III.—That Article 38, paragraph d) of Law 7593 empowers the Regulatory Authority to process administrative sanctioning procedures against public service providers who engage in “Unauthorized provision of public service (...)” by applying for this purpose the ordinary procedure established in the General Law of Public Administration and indicating that if the violation is proven, it may apply a fine of five to ten times the value of the damage caused that it determines, or, a fine equivalent to 5 to 20 minimum base salaries, established in Law 7337 of May 5, 1993, when it is unable to determine the damage.",rule_candidate,payoff,choice|payoff|position|scope,4,0,1,1,0,1,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
