6e50bb42a7856f81,203469,"III.—That Article 38, paragraph d) of Law 7593 empowers the Regulatory Authority to process administrative sanctioning procedures against public service providers who engage in “Unauthorized provision of public service (...)” by applying for this purpose the ordinary procedure established in the General Law of Public Administration and indicating that if the violation is proven, it may apply a fine of five to ten times the value of the damage caused that it determines, or, a fine equivalent to 5 to 20",it,explicit,may,permission,apply a fine of five,if the violation is proven,service,True,"III.—That Article 38, paragraph d) of Law 7593 empowers the Regulatory Authority to process administrative sanctioning procedures against public service providers who engage in “Unauthorized provision of public service (...)” by applying for this purpose the ordinary procedure established in the General Law of Public Administration and indicating that if the violation is proven, it may apply a fine of five to ten times the value of the damage caused that it determines, or, a fine equivalent to 5 to 20",rule_candidate,payoff,choice|payoff|position|scope,4,0,1,1,0,1,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
6e50bb42a7856f81,203474,"In this regard, the Law on Traffic on Public Land Roads, No. 9078 establishes the following provisions: I.—That in accordance with the provisions of article 9, paragraph 17) of the Regulations of Organization and Functions of the Regulatory Authority (RIOF), it is the responsibility of the General Regulator to order the opening of administrative procedures in which a fine is applied as a sanction, as well as to issue preparatory acts, precautionary measures and the final resolution, in addition to hearing any challenges that may be presented.",that,explicit,may,permission,presented,"in accordance with the provisions of article 9, paragraph 17) of the Regulations of Organization and Functions of the Regulatory Authority (RIOF), it is the responsibility of the General Regulator to order the opening of administrative procedures in which a fine is applied as a sanction, as well as to issue preparatory acts, precautionary measures and the final resolution, in addition to hearing any challenges that may be presented.",,True,"In this regard, the Law on Traffic on Public Land Roads, No. 9078 establishes the following provisions: I.—That in accordance with the provisions of article 9, paragraph 17) of the Regulations of Organization and Functions of the Regulatory Authority (RIOF), it is the responsibility of the General Regulator to order the opening of administrative procedures in which a fine is applied as a sanction, as well as to issue preparatory acts, precautionary measures and the final resolution, in addition to hearing any challenges that may be presented.",rule_candidate,payoff,choice|payoff|position,3,0,1,1,0,0,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
6e50bb42a7856f81,203477,"3. Article 38 of Law 7593 establishes that, if the commission of the violation is proven, those investigated are exposed to the imposition of a fine of 5 to 10 times the value of the damage caused or the equivalent of 5 to 20 minimum wages established in Law 7337 of May 5, 1993, in the event that the damage cannot be proven.",the damage,explicit,can,prohibition,proven,if the commission of the violation is proven,,True,"3. Article 38 of Law 7593 establishes that, if the commission of the violation is proven, those investigated are exposed to the imposition of a fine of 5 to 10 times the value of the damage caused or the equivalent of 5 to 20 minimum wages established in Law 7337 of May 5, 1993, in the event that the damage cannot be proven.",rule_candidate,payoff,choice|payoff|position,3,0,1,1,0,0,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
