7aa5a1124a71c7df,223778,"The design process should include appropriate mechanisms such as public consultation for AI systems posing a high risk to human rights, which may lead to redesign or the incorporation of mitigation strategies • Assessment, testing and evaluation: regular testing for human rights compliance from formulation of the initial proposal, through to design, development, prototyping and real- world implementation.",The design process,explicit,should,obligation,"include appropriate mechanisms such as public consultation for AI systems posing a high risk to human rights , which may lead to redesign or the incorporation of mitigation strategies • Assessment , testing and evaluation : regular testing for human rights compliance from formulation of the initial proposal",,AI systems,True,"The design process should include appropriate mechanisms such as public consultation for AI systems posing a high risk to human rights, which may lead to redesign or the incorporation of mitigation strategies • Assessment, testing and evaluation: regular testing for human rights compliance from formulation of the initial proposal, through to design, development, prototyping and real- world implementation.",rule_candidate,aggregation,aggregation|choice|information,3,0,0,1,1,0,1,0,0,0,,,,,,
7aa5a1124a71c7df,223780,"• Independent oversight, investigation and sanction: an independent, external, properly resourced and technically competent body should be established to oversee human rights compliance of the AI system, within a legally mandated institutional structure.","Independent oversight , investigation and sanction : an independent , external , properly resourced and technically competent body",explicit,should,obligation,established,within a legally mandated institutional structure,AI system,True,"• Independent oversight, investigation and sanction: an independent, external, properly resourced and technically competent body should be established to oversee human rights compliance of the AI system, within a legally mandated institutional structure.",rule_candidate,payoff,choice|payoff|position,3,0,1,1,0,0,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
