816f979923541208,258558,"The House bill contained a provision (sec. 540K) that would amend Article 6b(a)(2) of the Uniform Code of Military Justice (10 U.S.C. 802b(a)(2)), to provide that victims of offenses under the Uniform Code of Military Justice have the right to reasonable, ac- curate, and timely notice of a post-trial motion, filing, or hearing that may address the finding or sentence of a court-martial with respect to the accused, unseal privileged or private information of the victim, or result in the release of the accused.",that,explicit,may,permission,address the finding or sentence of a court - martial,with respect to the accused,,True,"The House bill contained a provision (sec. 540K) that would amend Article 6b(a)(2) of the Uniform Code of Military Justice (10 U.S.C. 802b(a)(2)), to provide that victims of offenses under the Uniform Code of Military Justice have the right to reasonable, ac- curate, and timely notice of a post-trial motion, filing, or hearing that may address the finding or sentence of a court-martial with respect to the accused, unseal privileged or private information of the victim, or result in the release of the accused.",rule_candidate,information,choice|information,2,0,0,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,,,,,,
