a3ef059eb9c069a8,337181,"117 Weeks Topics Covered Week 5-6: Attention Mechanisms and Transformer Models Introduction to attention mechanisms and their applications in NLP tasks Attention-based models, including Transformer and BERT Training Transformer-based models for text classification, sentiment analysis, and question - answering tasks Applications of Transformer-based models in NLP, such as language modeling and text generation Week 7-8: Generative Language Models Introduction to generative language models, including n-gram models and sequence models Auto-regressive models for text generation, including GPT-2 and GPT-3 Conditional language modeling with transformers and GANs Applications of generative language models, such as text completion, language translation, and question-answering Week 9-10: Advanced Topics in NLP Multi-task learning with NLP models Transfer learning in NLP, including pre-training and fine-tuning Domain adaptation with NLP models Adversarial attacks and defenses in NLP Week 11-12: Building Chatbots and Conversational AI Introduction to conversational AI and chatbot design Building rule-based chatbots using natural language understanding and generation tools End-to-end chatbot design using neural networks and sequence models Evaluation metrics for chatbots and conversational AI systems Week 13-14: Speech Recognition and Synthesis Introduction to speech recognition and speech synthesis Building automatic speech recognition (ASR) systems using deep neural networks Building text-to-speech (TTS) systems using WaveNet and Tacotron Applications of speech recognition and synthesis in NLP, such as speech translation and voice assistants Week 15-16: Project Final project involving the application of generative NLP models to a real -world problem, such as language translation, chatbot design, or speech recognition Students will be required to present their work in a final project report and demo",,implicit,required,obligation,present their work,in a