a796e2d0119e2b91,348292,"According to Section 14(1) of the Civil Servants Act (750/1994), a civil servant intentionally or through negligence violates the regulations to be observed in official duties or In order for a civil servant who has been assigned an official task related to automated decision-making, for example monitoring the system for a certain group of issues, to be held criminally liable, he must, according to Chapter 40 of the Criminal Code, when performing his duties: The liability of an individual civil servant is regulated in Chapter 4 of the Damages Act.",he,explicit,must,obligation,according,,system,True,"According to Section 14(1) of the Civil Servants Act (750/1994), a civil servant intentionally or through negligence violates the regulations to be observed in official duties or In order for a civil servant who has been assigned an official task related to automated decision-making, for example monitoring the system for a certain group of issues, to be held criminally liable, he must, according to Chapter 40 of the Criminal Code, when performing his duties: The liability of an individual civil servant is regulated in Chapter 4 of the Damages Act.",rule_candidate,payoff,choice|information|payoff,3,0,0,1,1,0,0,1,0,0,,,,,,
