d04efa0e02a93679,409753,"The exemption was granted based on false, erroneous, misleading, or incomplete information; (6) A serious incident occurred during the pilot, or there is a real concern that such an incident may occur. (b) Notwithstanding subsection (a), if the [Competent Authority] determines that there is an urgent need to revoke, restrict, or suspend the exemption in order to prevent immediate danger to the [protected interest], it may do so with immediate effect, provided that the exemption holder is given an opportunity to present its arguments as soon as possible after such revocation or suspension, and no later than [__] days from the date of the decision.",such an incident,explicit,may,permission,occur,"if the [ Competent Authority ] determines that there is an urgent need to revoke , restrict , or suspend the exemption in order to prevent immediate danger to the [ protected interest|Notwithstanding subsection (a), if the [Competent Authority] determines that there is an urgent need to revoke, restrict, or suspend the exemption in order to prevent immediate danger to the [protected interest], it may do so with immediate effect, provided that the exemption holder is given an opportunity to present its arguments as soon as possible after such revocation or suspension, and no later than [__] days from the date of the decision.",,True,"The exemption was granted based on false, erroneous, misleading, or incomplete information; (6) A serious incident occurred during the pilot, or there is a real concern that such an incident may occur. (b) Notwithstanding subsection (a), if the [Competent Authority] determines that there is an urgent need to revoke, restrict, or suspend the exemption in order to prevent immediate danger to the [protected interest], it may do so with immediate effect, provided that the exemption holder is given an opportunity to present its arguments as soon as possible after such revocation or suspension, and no later than [__] days from the date of the decision.",rule_candidate,information,choice|information|position,3,0,1,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,,,,,,
d04efa0e02a93679,409762,"16P “(a) The National Supervisor of Transportation shall publish to the public, on the website of the Ministry of Transportation and Road Safety, the following information, and may also publish additional details regarding the operation of autonomous vehicles which he deems necessary to bring to public attention, or publish all or part of them through other means: (1) Information on valid operating permits, including, inter alia, for each permit, the details of the permit holder, the operational area of the autonomous vehicle to which the permit applies, the areas in which the pilot operation is permitted under the permit, the number of autonomous vehicles covered by the permit, the validity period of the permit, and the material conditions set therein; (2) Notice of revocation, suspension, restriction, or refusal to renew an operating permit, under sections 16(k) and 16O(f).",The National Supervisor of Transportation,explicit,shall,obligation,publish “ ( a )|publish additional details,,,True,"16P “(a) The National Supervisor of Transportation shall publish to the public, on the website of the Ministry of Transportation and Road Safety, the following information, and may also publish additional details regarding the operation of autonomous vehicles which he deems necessary to bring to public attention, or publish all or part of them through other means: (1) Information on valid operating permits, including, inter alia, for each permit, the details of the permit holder, the operational area of the autonomous vehicle to which the permit applies, the areas in which the pilot operation is permitted under the permit, the number of autonomous vehicles covered by the permit, the validity period of the permit, and the material conditions set therein; (2) Notice of revocation, suspension, restriction, or refusal to renew an operating permit, under sections 16(k) and 16O(f).",rule_candidate,information,choice|information|position,3,0,1,1,1,0,0,0,0,0,,,,,,
d04efa0e02a93679,409774,"(b) The [Competent Authority] shall publish on its official website the following information, and may also publish additional details it considers should be brought to the public ’s attention, or publish them, in whole or in part, through additional means: (1) Information on valid exemptions granted under section [ ...], including the identity of the pilot operator , the number of consumers it may serve, the geographic area in which the pilot is to take place, to the extent such conditions were specified, the exemption period, and the material conditions set therein; (2) Notice of revocation, suspension, restriction, or refusal to renew an exemption; (3) In the event of a serious safety incident, the [Competent Authority] shall, as soon as possible following the incident, publish information about the incident, including details it considers should be brou ght to the public ’s attention.",( b ) The [ Competent Authority,explicit,shall,obligation,"publish the following information|publish additional details it considers should be brought to the public ’s attention , or publish them , in whole or in part , through additional means|publish information about the incident",,,True,"(b) The [Competent Authority] shall publish on its official website the following information, and may also publish additional details it considers should be brought to the public ’s attention, or publish them, in whole or in part, through additional means: (1) Information on valid exemptions granted under section [ ...], including the identity of the pilot operator , the number of consumers it may serve, the geographic area in which the pilot is to take place, to the extent such conditions were specified, the exemption period, and the material conditions set therein; (2) Notice of revocation, suspension, restriction, or refusal to renew an exemption; (3) In the event of a serious safety incident, the [Competent Authority] shall, as soon as possible following the incid