f12191ce5842c0db,460277,"In accordance with articles 11.3 and 40.2 of Law 38/2003, of 17 November, General Subsidies, the Administration granting the subsidy may require the coordinating entity or the rest of the participating entities to make a refund on a joint and several basis, even on a limited basis, in proportion, with respect to these, to the amounts assigned to each one, in accordance with the subsidised activities that they have undertaken to carry out, insofar as they all assume the condition of beneficiaries, not being conditioned by the fact that the non-compliance with the conditions established in the act granting the subsidy is attributable to only one of the beneficiaries, insofar as all of them are jointly responsible for the execution of a project under a cooperation regime.","General Subsidies ,",explicit,may,permission,require the coordinating entity or the rest of the participating entities,"In accordance with articles 11.3 and 40.2 of Law 38/2003, of 17 November, General Subsidies, the Administration granting the subsidy may require the coordinating entity or the rest of the participating entities to make a refund on a joint and several basis, even on a limited basis, in proportion, with respect to these, to the amounts assigned to each one, in accordance with the subsidised activities that they have undertaken to carry out, insofar as they all assume the condition of beneficiaries, not being conditioned by the fact that the non-compliance with the conditions established in the act granting the subsidy is attributable to only one of the beneficiaries, insofar as all of them are jointly responsible for the execution of a project under a cooperation regime.|In accordance with articles 11.3 and 40.2 of Law 38/2003",,True,"In accordance with articles 11.3 and 40.2 of Law 38/2003, of 17 November, General Subsidies, the Administration granting the subsidy may require the coordinating entity or the rest of the participating entities to make a refund 